{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcsSvc2hLQU9wn74GjL69","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Deployed a 3-node Elasticsearch 8.11.0 cluster in the `elasticsearch` namespace using only native resources:\n\n- **es-config** ConfigMap — `elasticsearch.yml` with discovery via the headless service, HTTP TLS from `es-http-tls`, and transport TLS from a newly generated `es-transport-certs` secret (self-signed CA, since node-to-node TLS needs a cert/key that wasn't provided).\n- **es-headless** (ClusterIP: None, `publishNotReadyAddresses: true`) for peer discovery, and **es-http** (ClusterIP) exposing port 9200.\n- **es-pdb** PodDisruptionBudget (`minAvailable: 2`).\n- **es** StatefulSet, 3 replicas, `es-0/1/2`, each with a 5Gi PVC (local-path storage class), init containers to fix data-dir ownership and bump `vm.max_map_count`, and `ELASTIC_PASSWORD` sourced from the `elastic-password` secret.\n\nVerified via the pre-existing `curl-test` pod:\n- `_cluster/health` → `status: green`, 3 nodes, 3 data nodes, reached over HTTPS at `https://es-http.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local:9200` with the CA from `es-http-tls`.\n- Write (`POST test-index/_doc/1`), read (`GET test-index/_doc/1`), and search all succeeded, with the index going green (primary + replica both active across nodes), confirming reads/writes work cluster-wide. Test index was cleaned up afterward."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":312,"cache_read_input_tokens":64223,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":312},"output_tokens":6,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6504e30c-91cb-4d1a-90e5-51a250f6a960","uuid":"80ca304a-e534-416e-b5c6-eb9e3d8093d6","request_id":"req_011CcsSvb1Rx1dQu5AY3tbyN"}
